    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Your article on Moscow omitted a number of important facts about the city:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Your article on Moscow omitted a number of important facts about the city:</p>
        <p>Public transport is readily available from Sheremetyevo airport by bus and jitney cab to the Moscow metro system. Taking a taxi involves the local transport mafia: there are no set rates, no meter usage and the ''official taxi office'' is simply the mafia operating indoors.</p>
        <p>The author seems to ignore a wide range of less expensive hotels starting with the Izmailovo Hotel complex by the flea market and clothing bazaar. It has hundreds of rooms at reasonable prices. Having stayed there often, I can vouch for the cleanliness and general efficiency of the hotel. There are also other Moscow hotels in the $65-to-$100 range, like the Leningradskaia.</p>
        <p>Readers should also know that instant travel to Russia is impossible. One needs an invitation and a visa. All can be done quite easily through an expeditor such as the Atlanta-based www.gotorussia.com.</p>
        <p>Philip Clendenning  Waltham, Mass.</p>
      </block>
